# ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_object (Data Source)

Reads a single S3 object's metadata, optionally a specific version, using the v2 API.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/data-sources/ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_object/data-source.tf"}}

## Schema

### Required

- `bucket_name` (String) Name of the bucket
- `object_key` (String) Object key (path within the bucket)
- `service_name` (String) Service name of the resource representing the id of the cloud project

### Optional

- `version_id` (String) Version identifier. When set, the data source reads metadata for that specific version.

### Read-Only

- `e_tag` (String) Entity tag (ETag) of the object
- `is_common_prefix` (Boolean) Whether this entry is a common-prefix grouping rather than an object
- `is_delete_marker` (Boolean) Whether this version is a delete marker
- `is_latest` (Boolean) Whether this version is the latest version of the object
- `key` (String) Object key as returned by the API
- `last_modified` (String) Date and time at which the object was last modified
- `legal_hold` (String) Current legal hold status of the object (`ON`, `OFF`)
- `replication_status` (String) Replication status (`COMPLETED`, `FAILED`, `NONE`, `PENDING`, `REPLICA`)
- `response_version_id` (String) Version identifier returned by the API for the object
- `restore_status` (Attributes) Restore status for objects stored in archive tiers (see [below for nested schema](#nestedatt--restore_status))
- `retention` (Attributes) Current retention (object lock) configuration (see [below for nested schema](#nestedatt--retention))
- `size` (Number) Size of the object in bytes
- `storage_class` (String) Storage class (`DEEP_ARCHIVE`, `GLACIER`, `GLACIER_IR`, `HIGH_PERF`, `INTELLIGENT_TIERING`, `ONEZONE_IA`, `STANDARD`, `STANDARD_IA`)

<a id="nestedatt--restore_status"></a>

### Nested Schema for `restore_status`

Read-Only:

- `expire_date` (String) Date and time at which the restored copy expires
- `in_progress` (Boolean) Whether a restore operation is currently in progress

<a id="nestedatt--retention"></a>

### Nested Schema for `retention`

Read-Only:

- `mode` (String) Retention mode applied to the object (`COMPLIANCE`, `GOVERNANCE`, `NONE`)
- `retain_until_date` (String) Date and time until which the object is retained
